// Distinguishing features

Table: feature
a [|long|thin|curved|faded] scar across [|the cheek|the chin|the brow|the throat|the back of the hand]
[|one clouded eye|a missing earlobe|a brand on the wrist|two fingers missing on the left hand|a nose broken and poorly set]
[|elaborate tattoos on both forearms|a single tattoo on the neck|a tattoo partially hidden by the collar]
[|a persistent slight limp|unusually calloused hands|nails kept slightly too long|a habit of clicking the knuckles]
nothing remarkable — deliberately forgettable-looking
[|a beauty spot|unusually sharp teeth|heterochromia — two different eye colours|a birthmark on the jaw]

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Racial abilities
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: racial_Human
Versatile: Gains one additional skill proficiency and one additional tool proficiency of choice.
Determined: Once per short rest, can re-roll one ability check and take the higher result.
Resourceful: Once per long rest, gains Inspiration without a die roll.

Table: racial_Elf
Darkvision 60 ft. Fey Ancestry: advantage on saving throws against being charmed; magic cannot put them to sleep.
Trance: Instead of sleeping, meditates for 4 hours (equivalent of 8 hours rest). Immune to magical sleep.
Keen Senses: Proficiency in Perception. Darkvision 60 ft. Fey Ancestry.

Table: racial_Dwarf
Darkvision 60 ft. Dwarven Resilience: advantage on saving throws against poison; resistance to poison damage.
Stonecunning: Double proficiency bonus on History checks related to stonework.
Dwarven Toughness: HP maximum increases by 1 per level. Darkvision 60 ft.

Table: racial_Half-Orc
Darkvision 60 ft. Relentless Endurance: Once per long rest, drop to 1 HP instead of 0.
Savage Attacks: On a critical melee hit, roll one damage die extra.
Menacing: Proficiency in Intimidation. Darkvision 60 ft.

Table: racial_Halfling
Lucky: When rolling a 1 on a d20, re-roll and use the new result.
Brave: Advantage on saving throws against being frightened.
Nimbleness: Can move through the space of any creature at least one size larger.

Table: racial_Gnome
Darkvision 60 ft. Gnome Cunning: advantage on all INT, WIS, CHA saving throws against magic.
Artificer's Lore: Double proficiency on History checks related to magical, alchemical, or technological items.
Natural Illusionist: Knows the Minor Illusion cantrip (INT).

Table: racial_Tiefling
Darkvision 60 ft. Hellish Resistance: Resistance to fire damage.
Infernal Legacy: Knows Thaumaturgy cantrip; at 3rd level gains Hellish Rebuke; at 5th level gains Darkness.
Legacy of Dis: Knows the Disguise Self spell (1/day) in addition to standard infernal spells.

Table: racial_Dragonborn
Draconic Ancestry: resistance to the damage type associated with scale colour.
Breath Weapon: Exhales a {1d6 + 3}-ft [|cone|line] of elemental energy (DC 8 + CON mod + proficiency; {2d6} damage, scaling with level).
Damage Resistance tied to ancestry type.

Table: racial_Half-Elf
Darkvision 60 ft. Fey Ancestry: advantage vs charm; magic cannot sleep them.
Skill Versatility: Gains proficiency in any 2 skills of choice.
Otherworldly: Advantage on Perception. Darkvision 60 ft.

Table: racial_Aasimar
Darkvision 60 ft. Celestial Resistance: Resistance to necrotic and radiant damage.
Healing Hands: Touch to restore {1d4 + level} HP (1/long rest). Languages: Common, Celestial.
Divine Magic: Knows the Light cantrip. Once per long rest, can cast Cure Wounds at 1st level.

