// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Personality traits
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: personality
I always have a plan for what to do when things go wrong.
I am incredibly slow to trust, but those who earn it receive unwavering loyalty.
I ask too many questions and never know when to stop.
I have a crude sense of humour and laugh at the most inappropriate times.
I fall in and out of love easily and am currently enamoured with someone nearby.
I always prefer the direct approach — diplomacy is for those who lack conviction.
I like to collect odd trinkets wherever I travel.
I judge people by their actions, not their words.
I tell stories of my exploits at every opportunity — some of them are even true.
I'm haunted by memories of war and can be startled by sudden sounds.
I watch over my friends as if they were a litter of newborn pups.
I have a weakness for flattery — it is an embarrassingly effective tool against me.
I never pass up a meal, and I am always starving after a good fight.
I'm always calm, no matter what the situation. I never raise my voice or let my emotions control me.
I'm full of witty aphorisms and have a proverb for every occasion.
I am utterly serene, even in the face of disaster.
I feel tremendous empathy for all who suffer.
The best way to get me to do something is to tell me I can't do it.
I'm confident in my own abilities and do what I can to instil the same confidence in others.
I bluntly say what other people are hinting at or talking around.
I am reckless — I act first and worry about consequences later.
I am suspicious of strangers and expect the worst of them.
I can stare down a hell hound without flinching.
I once ran twenty-five miles without stopping to warn my people of an approaching army. I'd do it again.

Table: ideal
Greater Good: our purpose is to serve the people around us.
Logic: emotions must not cloud our sense of right and wrong.
Freedom: chains, whether literal or figurative, must be broken.
Power: one day I will rule these lands — by merit, not birthright.
Sincerity: there is no good in pretending to be something you are not.
Change: we must upend the old ways in favour of something better.
Aspiration: I seek to prove myself worthy of a great destiny.
Live and Let Live: meddling in others' affairs only leads to trouble.
Redemption: there is a spark of good in everyone worth fanning into flame.
Beauty: when I perform, I make the world better than it was.
Creativity: the world is in need of new ideas and bold action.
Greed: I'm only in it for the gold — everything else is secondary.
Independence: I must earn my way in the world. No one gives me anything for free.
Might: in life as in war, the stronger force wins.
Nation: my city, nation, or people are all that matter.
People: I'm committed to the people I care about, not to ideals.
Honesty: art should reflect the soul; it should come from within.
Fairness: no one should get preferential treatment before the law.
Community: it is the duty of all civilised people to strengthen the bonds of community.
Self-Knowledge: if you know yourself, there is nothing left to know.

Table: bond
I would die to recover a family heirloom stolen years ago.
I protect those who cannot protect themselves.
Someone I loved died because of a mistake I made — I will never repeat it.
My honour is my life; nothing will compromise it.
I owe everything to a mentor who believed in me when no one else did.
I'm trying to pay off an old debt — one coin at a time.
I want to find the person who destroyed my home and make them pay.
A secret society once helped me; now I repay the favour whenever I can.
I escaped my guilty past by remaking myself — no one from before must ever find me.
My isolation gave me great insight into a great evil that only I can destroy.
I enter every room looking for the best escape route — I have never been caught unprepared.
I would sacrifice everything to prevent the catastrophe that took my family.
I entered a solemn pact with a powerful entity; I will not fail it.
I am the last member of my family. I must ensure our name lives on.
My comrades-in-arms saved my life. I would die for them.
An injury to the common folk is an injury to me — I will fight it wherever I find it.

Table: flaw
I have trouble keeping my true feelings hidden.
I am convinced that no one can ever truly understand me.
I am overly proud of my accomplishments and dismiss those of others.
I have a weakness for shiny objects — or any treasure, really.
Once I set my mind to something, I am dangerously stubborn.
I have difficulty trusting anyone, even my closest allies.
I often make promises I am not entirely sure I can keep.
I am quick to assume the worst of people.
I have a weakness for the vices of the city — especially the drink.
I'll do anything to win fame and renown.
I become confused, frantic, or terrified if I lose access to my ritual tools.
I follow orders, even if I think they're wrong.
I'm not great at sharing my feelings; I bottle everything up.
I turn tail and run when things look bad.
A secret fear makes me freeze at the worst possible moments.
I say whatever people want to hear rather than tell the truth.
I judge others harshly and demand perfect obedience to the letter of the law.
I am slow to trust and rarely open up, even to friends.

