// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Backstory hooks
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: backstory
You grew up in the shadow of [|a burned village|a conquered city|a legendary family name|a monastery since destroyed], which still shapes who you are.
Someone you trusted [|betrayed you|died protecting you|disappeared without explanation|sold you out to an enemy] — and you have never truly recovered.
You carry a secret: [|you witnessed a crime that powerful people want buried|your true identity is not what your companions believe|a past deed that would change how your allies see you].
A [|dying mentor|fallen soldier|captured prisoner|wounded stranger] once told you something that has haunted you ever since.
You swore an oath — [|to protect a certain bloodline|to find a relic|to avenge a specific name|to never return home until you have achieved something worthy] — and you have not broken it yet.
You were chosen — by a god, a prophecy, a secret order, or a dying noble — for a purpose you don't fully understand.
You came close to death [|on a battlefield|in a dungeon|during a ritual gone wrong|at the hands of someone you thought was a friend] and have never been the same since.
Something follows you — [|an entity you cannot explain|a recurring dream|a stranger who always seems to be one step behind|a mark on your skin that appeared overnight].
You owe a debt — [|to a thieves' guild|to a divine power|to a family that sheltered you|to a lord who pardoned a crime] — that you cannot yet repay.
You are looking for [|a person|an artefact|a place|an answer] that most people believe no longer exists.
